#20201
Into the Forest~
You continue to follow the path deeper into the Forest of Saddness. You
certainly can see how the name came about: the trees seem to droop as if
they themselves are crying, and the songs of birds seem to be sad rather
than cheerful. Not only that, you notice that no matter what time of day it
is, the forest seems to be in perpetual twilight, dusk, or dawn. Something
else you notice is that when the wind blows you are sure you can hear the
sounds of someone crying.
  The pathway continues up ahead towards the north. You think you can see
some movement up ahead, as well as the sounds of someone sniffing.
~
